  "text": "As we argue in [CITATION_1] (in a context different but in this respect comparable to the present one), besides the latter metalevel classes, additional ones are in fact necessary to support distributed concerns such as e.g. objects and operations delivering. Especially noteworthy among them are Locator and ServerProxy, which are used respectively to store the location of distributed objects, and to receive data and commands on the server side.",
